{{main|Timeline of the 2011 Egyptian revolution under Supreme Council of the Armed Forces#September}}
On Friday, 9 September 2011, hundreds of Egyptian protesters began gathering outside the of the Israeli embassy in Giza. Around 18:30 pm (local time) the Egyptian protesters began to demolish the concrete security wall surrounding the building, which the Egyptian authorities set up following the last intense protests which were held in front of the Israeli embassy building in August.
